{"id": 4571, "title": "Ticket #4571: can't set a .txt extension for the logs on Windows", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe config code that detects that a file path type assignment in a config file is the same as the default value is confused by the addition of an extension to the filename,  so you cannot set\n\n<p></p><pre>    MASTER_LOG=$(LOG)\\MasterLog.txt\n</pre>\n\n<p>because it thinks this is the same as the default of <code>$(LOG)\\MasterLog</code>. While\n\n</p><p></p><pre>    MASTER_LOG=$(LOG)\\MysteryLog.txt\n</pre>\n\n<p>Works because the basename is also different.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-Sep-04 13:54:34 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\nIt turns out that the bug was that you could not set the log filename on Windows to ANY value for which the default value was a prefix or suffix. This bug doesn't affect Linux because it uses a different function to compare paths.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Sep-18 09:55</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=41190\">[41190]</a></span>: 8.2.3 version history item edit <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4571\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4571'); return false;\" title=\"can't set a .txt extension for the logs on Windows\">#4571</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Sep-09 16:14</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=41129\">[41129]</a></span>: Version history for 8.2.3 bugfixes <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/t